OL,4,Cas they believed Covid was a
OL,5,Cconspiracy'
OL,7,F"She was crying, saying, 'Jemma, the
OL,8,Fresidents are poorly, I don't know
OL,9,Fwhat to do'," Mrs Turner said.
OL,11,F"I said, 'Where's the nurse?' and she
OL,12,Fsaid, 'He's refusing to wear a mask
OL,13,Fand he's walking around the home and
OL,14,Fhe's saying that Covid is a
OL,15,Fconspiracy'.
OL,17,F"She said she thought he was positive
OL,18,Ftoo and she'd had an argument with him
OL,19,Fabout doing testing.
