OL,4,Cas they believed Covid was a
OL,5,Cconspiracy'
OL,7,F"He told me he would. All of this was
OL,8,Fwritten out on a supervision form
OL,9,Fabout mask wearing and daily testing
OL,10,Fand making sure he had his weekly test
OL,11,Fbecause there were occasions where we
OL,12,Fhad to chase him up to come and do his
OL,13,Ftest.
OL,15,F"The next time when I spoke to him, I
OL,16,Ftold him he was not wearing his mask,
OL,17,Fand he needed to and that's when he
OL,18,Fsaid he had medical issues and he was
OL,19,Ffinding it hard to breathe.
